	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=/cgi-bin/mrate.pl name=f100351455824652>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=>bash needs a fix</a> <a id=fs8 href=#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Fri, Oct 19th 2:02 PM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=105420><span id= >Diak</span></a><br><span id=notbold>8 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [2.50]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p> As a Paladin i must say this is one hella of nice shield . That said lets get down to the rat killing.. our class will never be up to speed IMHO untill the day VI wakes up to the fact that our BASH skill is and has always been less then it should be. (for the unwashed) what is bash ?<br> bash is the skill to stun and do damge to one's <br>target&nbsp;&nbsp;by use of a shield, sounds easy huh?.<br>well its not , first off its slow and there is no way to make it faster its timed  it has a set delay. it also has a set max damage at lvl 53 with my skill maxed i have never had a bash hit for more then 20 points. Also the stun is random and not bassed on the damge at all, i have stunned with one point of damge and not stunned with 18 points .(yes i know for VI to start making sense would in fact scare us all at this point ) about the only thing that does work with this skill is the spell casting interrupts <br> most but not all times a good paladin with a shield (any shield will do) can keep a caster from doing his job to any great effect even in the high end game. <br> Paladins are more then this, and our skill at bash should reflect that so how to fix this ?<br> thats easy ....ok it only took me about 20 lvl's and over 100 days played to come up with something that would work<br> bash should = level + the AC of the shield = the base damge that a bash attack could do, note that the skill check done as part of all attacks would then come into play ,ok this would work for players till about lvl 12 and then it gets out of hand rather fast  so post lvl 12 the way it would work would be like this  bash= 1/2 the players level+ the ac of the shield - the wieght of the shield  <br> ok the first thing to be said is this mak